Discore aims to fully implement two sides of the Discord API: the HTTP API, and the realtime WebSocket API. It's designed for creating Discord bot applications, as well as applications that do not require realtime data.
Please note! Discore is not an official Discord API wrapper.

FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
- Removed DiscordHttpErrorCode.BadRequest.
- Fixed rate limited routes not taking major parameters into account. - Fixed CreateInvite's maxAge argument causing a bad request. - Fixed CreateGuildChannelParameters not treating all parameters as optional. - Fixed DiscoreCacheTable.GetEnumerator throwing a NotImplementedException in some cases.
- Added ability to create guilds. - Added missing DiscordPermission enum values. - Added ability to set topic when creating text channels. - Added missing Id property to OverwriteParameters. - Added DiscoreTypeCache.Id. - Added implicit Snowflake <-> ulong operator. - Added DiscordHttpErrorCode enum value for error 50021.
And more...
